    "description": {
      "value": "<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">You invoke Tor to cleave the sky with his mighty war axe. Clouds roil high above, and after 1d10 rounds, either a Downpour, Rain, Snow, or Blizzard (as appropriate) begins. Consult the <em>Enemy in Shadows Companion </em>on page 33 for the weather. <em>Cleave the Sky </em>may only be attempted if the sky is already overcast. With +4 SL you may choose the weather.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">This Miracle is not bound by typical Miracles Limitations (<em>Core Book</em>, page 217), may be enacted as many times as you wish and does not prevent other Miracles from being used.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></p>"
